column49: I am disappointed this year with the way orders are being submitted. Not all families have access to place an order online and the paper order forms turned in to the teacher were better. I am also disappointed in the fact that the prices of books have risen to a point where a lot of families are choosing not to order. I liked the round numbers of the pricing better...$2.00 instead of 1.99 for example. As a teacher I have been providing my students with free books from Scholastic for many years. I was able to do this through donations and purchasing the $1.00 books. It is harder to get doantions now and books prices have doubled. The elimination of the dollar book store was quite unfortunate and the fact that we have to check weekly for thre $2 book option is difficult. There are a hundred other student related tasks I do during the day, remembering to check weekly is hard. I sent my holiday order home as soon as I got it due to our school schedule.  I had already manually submitted a fall order since I did not understand the new system.  My class ordered almost $100 of holiday books before the fall due date, and my holiday order automatically submitted with the fall order because I send the flyers early not realizing that it was going to automatically submit.  The reason that I am angry is because I got screwed out of my $10 to spend now with my holiday order since it technically counted as part of my fall order.  I doubt I will get $25 of more orders before the holiday due date, so I will not get to use the perk that I earned by selling your books for you.  I reached out to a live chat customer representative who was very unhelpful and not willing to help me get the $10 I deserve.  Very unhappy.
